The paper deals with the problem of single-source shortest paths in the CONGEST model of distributed computing, which involves a network of nodes communicating with each other to solve a problem. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves algorithms for graph theory and network analysis, which are covered by the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper involves randomized algorithms and complexity analysis, which are covered by the categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Algorithms (cs.AL).
